<paragraph pageId="2" pageNumber="3">Comments.</paragraph>
<paragraph pageId="2" pageNumber="3">
Based on the principle of priority, 
<taxonomicName class="Pucciniomycetes" genus="Hemileia" higherTaxonomySource="CoL" kingdom="Fungi" lsidName="Hemileia deightonii" order="Pucciniales" pageId="2" pageNumber="3" phylum="Basidiomycota" rank="species" species="deightonii">Hemileia deightonii</taxonomicName>
is the correct name for this species. This name had been placed in 
<taxonomicName class="Pucciniomycetes" genus="Uredo" higherTaxonomySource="CoL" kingdom="Fungi" lsidName="Uredo" order="Pucciniales" pageId="2" pageNumber="3" phylum="Basidiomycota" rank="genus">Uredo</taxonomicName>
because of the lack of teliospores as dictated by the ICBN in effect at that time but is now allowed by the ICN.
</paragraph>
